result.name: Screening for variants in feline LHCGR gene
result.description: Disorders of sex development (DSD) are congenital conditions in which the chromosomal, gonadal or phentypical sex is atypical. The DSD are usually responsible for sterility or infertility and thus their occurrence in domestic animals is considered as an important breeding problem. The aim of the project is searching for genetic variants in a candidate gene LHCGR using Sanger sequencing
result.center: Poznan University of Life Sciences, Poznan, Poland
